Vice President Biden spoke with Prime Minister Binali Yildirim of Turkey to express condolences for the recent terrorist attacks in Istanbul and Midyat. They both condemned the acts of violence and pledged to continue their cooperation in combating terrorism. Vice President Biden also congratulated Prime Minister Yildirim on his leadership role and emphasized the importance of the U.S.-Turkey partnership. They also discussed their support for efforts in Cyprus to reach a reunification agreement for the island.